Goal: build and verify FSCRUD-01 with deterministic senior scaffold and contract tests

memory:
  fscrud_workspace
  fscrud_task
  fscrud_model_policy

flow:
  remember key="fscrud_workspace" value="workspace/fscrud-01"
  remember key="fscrud_task" value="TASK.md"
  remember key="fscrud_model_policy" value="local Ollama model; runtime speed is telemetry, not a success metric"

  let task_contract = "FSCRUD-01 field-service work order tracker. Build customers, assets, and work_orders with list/create/read/edit/detail/delete flows; enforce customer-asset-work_order references, asset/customer mismatch rejection, completedAt/status rules, safe deletes, seed data, domain validation tests, integration-style tests for each entity family, README, run-manifest.json, and verification-report.md. Prefer a small deterministic Node CommonJS implementation with src/domain.js, src/server.js, public/index.html, and __tests__/domain.contract.test.js before adding framework weight. src/domain.js must be CommonJS only, with no export keyword and no update* function aliases. Task contract: ${fscrud_task}."

  run: node -e "const fs=require('fs');const cp=require('child_process');const paths=['experiments/fullstack-crud-comparison/scaffold/write-scaffold-contract.cjs','../../../../../fullstack-crud-comparison/scaffold/write-scaffold-contract.cjs'];const script=paths.find((p)=>fs.existsSync(p));if(!script){console.error('scaffold script missing');process.exit(1)}const r=cp.spawnSync(process.execPath,[script,'workspace/fscrud-01'],{stdio:'inherit'});process.exit(r.status??1)" [timeout 60]
  try
    run: node -e "const fs=require('fs'); for (const p of ['workspace/fscrud-01/package.json','workspace/fscrud-01/CONTRACT.md','workspace/fscrud-01/src/domain.js','workspace/fscrud-01/__tests__/domain.contract.test.js','workspace/fscrud-01/data/seed.json']) if(!fs.existsSync(p)){ console.error('missing '+p); process.exit(1); } const t=fs.readFileSync('workspace/fscrud-01/src/domain.js','utf8'); for (const term of ['listCustomers','createCustomer','readCustomer','detailCustomer','editCustomer','deleteCustomer','listAssets','createAsset','readAsset','detailAsset','editAsset','deleteAsset','listWorkOrders','createWorkOrder','readWorkOrder','detailWorkOrder','editWorkOrder','deleteWorkOrder']) if(!t.includes(term)){ console.error('missing export '+term); process.exit(1); }" [timeout 60]
  end

  prompt: Work only in ${fscrud_workspace}. Senior Card: GOAL implement the src/domain.js foundation plus customers and assets only. FILE src/domain.js only. ACTION read_file src/domain.js, then write_file src/domain.js with one complete replacement. MUST use CommonJS only: no export keyword, no export const, no export default, and no ESM syntax. MUST end with module.exports assigning exactly these exported function names: reset, listCustomers, createCustomer, readCustomer, detailCustomer, editCustomer, deleteCustomer, listAssets, createAsset, readAsset, detailAsset, editAsset, deleteAsset, listWorkOrders, createWorkOrder, readWorkOrder, detailWorkOrder, editWorkOrder, deleteWorkOrder. MUST NOT rename editCustomer/editAsset/editWorkOrder to updateCustomer/updateAsset/updateWorkOrder. MUST implement reset, in-memory stores, ids, clone safety, and list/create/read/detail/edit/delete for customers and assets. MUST validate asset.customerId exists. KEEP work_order functions present; they may remain placeholders for the next card. KEEP package.json, CONTRACT.md, __tests__/domain.contract.test.js, data/seed.json, public/index.html, README.md, run-manifest.json, and verification-report.md unchanged. CHECK use the review probe; do not run broad tests yet. Task contract: ${task_contract}.
  review strict criteria: "The domain foundation must support customer and asset CRUD while preserving the exact CommonJS export surface." grounded-by 'node -e "const fs=require(\"fs\");const source=fs.readFileSync(\"workspace/fscrud-01/src/domain.js\",\"utf8\");const flat=source.replace(/\\s+/g,\" \");for(const term of [\"export \",\"export const\",\"export default\",\"updateCustomer\",\"updateAsset\",\"updateWorkOrder\"])if(flat.includes(term)){console.error(\"forbidden_domain_shape:\"+term);process.exit(1)}if(!source.includes(\"module.exports\")){console.error(\"missing module.exports\");process.exit(1)}for(const term of [\"listCustomers\",\"detailCustomer\",\"editCustomer\",\"listAssets\",\"detailAsset\",\"editAsset\",\"listWorkOrders\",\"detailWorkOrder\",\"editWorkOrder\"])if(!source.includes(term)){console.error(\"missing_required_name:\"+term);process.exit(1)}const d=require(\"./workspace/fscrud-01/src/domain.js\");d.reset();const c=d.createCustomer({name:\"Acme\"});if(d.listCustomers().length!==1)throw new Error(\"customer list failed\");if(d.readCustomer(c.id).name!==\"Acme\")throw new Error(\"customer read failed\");if(d.detailCustomer(c.id).id!==c.id)throw new Error(\"customer detail failed\");if(d.editCustomer(c.id,{name:\"Acme 2\"}).name!==\"Acme 2\")throw new Error(\"customer edit failed\");const a=d.createAsset({customerId:c.id,name:\"Truck 7\"});if(d.listAssets().length!==1)throw new Error(\"asset list failed\");if(d.readAsset(a.id).customerId!==c.id)throw new Error(\"asset read failed\");if(d.detailAsset(a.id).id!==a.id)throw new Error(\"asset detail failed\");if(d.editAsset(a.id,{name:\"Truck 7A\"}).name!==\"Truck 7A\")throw new Error(\"asset edit failed\");for(const fn of [\"listWorkOrders\",\"createWorkOrder\",\"readWorkOrder\",\"detailWorkOrder\",\"editWorkOrder\",\"deleteWorkOrder\"])if(typeof d[fn]!==\"function\")throw new Error(\"missing \"+fn);d.deleteAsset(a.id);d.deleteCustomer(c.id);"' max 2
    prompt: Repair src/domain.js only. FAILED_CHECK: customer/asset foundation probe or CommonJS export-shape probe. ALLOWED_FILES: src/domain.js. ACTION read_file src/domain.js, then write_file src/domain.js with one complete CommonJS replacement. MUST remove every export keyword and every updateCustomer/updateAsset/updateWorkOrder alias. MUST end with module.exports assigning the exact required names. Keep every CommonJS export name present. Critique: ${_review_critique}
  end

  prompt: Work only in ${fscrud_workspace}. Senior Card: GOAL finish work_orders in src/domain.js. FILE src/domain.js only. ACTION read_file src/domain.js, then write_file src/domain.js. MUST keep CommonJS only: no export keyword, no ESM syntax, no updateCustomer/updateAsset/updateWorkOrder aliases, and preserve the exact module.exports function names from the previous card. MUST keep passing customer and asset behavior unchanged. MUST implement list/create/read/detail/edit/deleteWorkOrder. MUST enforce customerId, assetId, asset/customer mismatch, status values open/scheduled/in_progress/completed/cancelled, completedAt rules, and priority values low/normal/urgent on both createWorkOrder and editWorkOrder. MUST reject completed without completedAt and non-completed with completedAt. MUST make deleteCustomer and deleteAsset prevent active dangling work_order references by throwing when active work_orders reference them. KEEP package.json, CONTRACT.md, __tests__/domain.contract.test.js, data/seed.json, public/index.html, README.md, run-manifest.json, and verification-report.md unchanged. CHECK cd workspace/fscrud-01 && npm test. REPAIR write_file only work_order behavior or direct regressions shown by the tests. Task contract: ${task_contract}.
  review strict criteria: "The full domain implementation must pass executable contract tests without weakening tests or package scripts." grounded-by "cd workspace/fscrud-01 && npm test" max 3
    prompt: Repair src/domain.js only. Use this senior repair card. FAILED_CHECK: npm test or domain contract. ALLOWED_FILES: src/domain.js. DO_NOT_TOUCH: package.json, CONTRACT.md, __tests__/domain.contract.test.js, data/seed.json. ACTION read_file src/domain.js, then write_file src/domain.js with only the missing behavior shown in stdout/stderr fixed. Preserve CommonJS module.exports, every exact export name, and passing behavior. Critique: ${_review_critique}
  end

  prompt: Work only in ${fscrud_workspace}. Senior Card: GOAL implement minimal HTTP routes in src/server.js using the passing domain module. FILE src/server.js only. ACTION read_file src/server.js, then write_file src/server.js. MUST expose GET collection, POST collection, GET /:id, GET /:id/detail, PATCH /:id, and DELETE /:id routes for customers, assets, and work_orders. MUST return JSON errors for validation failures. KEEP domain tests passing and do not edit src/domain.js unless npm test names a direct integration break. CHECK cd workspace/fscrud-01 && npm test. Task contract: ${task_contract}.
  review strict criteria: "Server slice must mention all route families and preserve passing domain contracts." grounded-by 'node -e "const fs=require(\"fs\");const t=fs.readFileSync(\"workspace/fscrud-01/src/server.js\",\"utf8\").toLowerCase(); for (const term of [\"customers\",\"assets\",\"work_orders\",\"list\",\"create\",\"read\",\"edit\",\"detail\",\"delete\"]) if(!t.includes(term)){ console.error(\"missing server term \"+term); process.exit(1); }" && cd workspace/fscrud-01 && npm test' max 2
    prompt: Repair src/server.js only unless npm test proves src/domain.js regressed. ACTION read_file src/server.js, then write_file src/server.js. Preserve the passing contract tests. Critique: ${_review_critique}
  end

  prompt: Work only in ${fscrud_workspace}. Senior Card: GOAL make public/index.html visibly exercise the API. FILE public/index.html only. ACTION read_file public/index.html, then write_file public/index.html. MUST include visible buttons/forms wired with fetch calls for list/create/read/edit/detail/delete for customers, assets, and work_orders. MUST mention customerId, assetId, status, completedAt, and priority. KEEP tests and source files unchanged. Task contract: ${task_contract}.
  review strict criteria: "UI must visibly cover entities, CRUD actions, and relationship/status fields." grounded-by 'node -e "const fs=require(\"fs\");const t=fs.readFileSync(\"workspace/fscrud-01/public/index.html\",\"utf8\").toLowerCase(); for (const term of [\"customers\",\"assets\",\"work_orders\",\"list\",\"create\",\"read\",\"edit\",\"detail\",\"delete\",\"customerid\",\"assetid\",\"status\",\"completedat\",\"priority\"]) if(!t.includes(term)){ console.error(\"missing ui term \"+term); process.exit(1); }"' max 2
    prompt: Repair public/index.html only. ACTION read_file public/index.html, then write_file public/index.html. Add the missing visible field or operation labels from the critique. Critique: ${_review_critique}
  end

  prompt: Work only in ${fscrud_workspace}. Senior Card: GOAL finalize README.md, run-manifest.json, and verification-report.md honestly. FILES README.md, run-manifest.json, verification-report.md only. ACTION read_file each allowed file, then write_file only those files. MUST document npm test, npm start, model/runner placeholders if unknown, and whether the verifier was actually run. KEEP code, tests, seed, and UI unchanged. Task contract: ${task_contract}.
  review strict criteria: "Final workspace must pass tests and the hardened FSCRUD verifier." grounded-by 'node -e "const fs=require(\"fs\");const cp=require(\"child_process\");const paths=[\"experiments/fullstack-crud-comparison/verification/verify-fullstack-crud-workspace.mjs\",\"../../../../../fullstack-crud-comparison/verification/verify-fullstack-crud-workspace.mjs\"];const script=paths.find((p)=>fs.existsSync(p));if(!script){console.error(\"verifier script missing\");process.exit(1)}const r=cp.spawnSync(process.execPath,[script,\"--workspace\",\"workspace/fscrud-01\",\"--json\"],{encoding:\"utf8\",stdio:\"inherit\"});process.exit(r.status??1)"' max 2
    prompt: Repair only README.md, run-manifest.json, verification-report.md, or the exact source file named by verifier stdout/stderr. Do not weaken tests, seed, package scripts, or contract files. Critique: ${_review_critique}
  end

  run: node -e "require('fs').writeFileSync('workspace/fscrud-01/.pl-scaffold-contract-complete','ok\n')" [timeout 60]

done when:
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/package.json
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/CONTRACT.md
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/README.md
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/src/domain.js
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/src/server.js
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/public/index.html
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/__tests__/domain.contract.test.js
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/data/seed.json
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/run-manifest.json
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/verification-report.md
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/.pl-scaffold-contract-complete
